Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, bilirubinuria), suggesting possible renal dysfunction. Elevated chloride and low COâ‚‚ may indicate mild metabolic acidosis. Blood glucose is normal, but HbA1c is unexpectedly low-potentially due to anemia or lab error. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend further renal evaluation and correlation with clinical findings.
